@Dan and @Michael - On Sunday, Biden met with Wilmington, Delaware demonstrators in the streets . On Monday, he met with black leaders then held a virtual roundtable with the mayors of Los Angeles, Chicago, Atlanta, St. Paul and Minneapolis.

 On Monday, Pelosi and Schumer issued a joint statement condemning the tear gassing of peaceful protesters outside of the White House.  

On Monday, Trump cleared his path with armed police and tear gas to walk  a safe and well-guarded path so that he could  hold a Bible up in front of a boarded Church with a belligerent  pout on his face. All hail the King.

First they came for the socialist, and I did not speak out- because I was not a socialist;

Then they came for the trade unionist, and I did not speak out- because I was not a trade unionist;

Then they came for the Jews, and I did not speak out -  because I was not a Jew;

Then they came for me- and there was no one left to speak for me.

                              Martin Niemoller (speaking after WW2)
